          "question": "A: In Maryland, the general statute of limitations for most personal injury claims is three years from the date of the injury. However, there are important exceptions. For instance, if the injury is not immediately discoverable, the \"discovery rule\" may apply, starting the three-year clock from when the injury was or should have been discovered. For minors, the statute of limitations is tolled until they reach 18, giving them until their 21st birthday to file a claim. Medical malpractice cases also have a specific outer limit of five years from the date of injury, regardless of discovery. It is crucial to consult with an attorney to determine the exact deadline for your specific case [1].",
