          "question": "What is the statute of limitations in Tennessee?",
          "answer": "In Tennessee, the general statute of limitations for most personal injury claims is **one year** from the date the injury occurred or was discovered [1]. This means you have a limited time to file a lawsuit to seek compensation. There are some rare exceptions that can extend this deadline, such as for minors, individuals deemed incompetent, or if the at-fault party leaves the state. However, it is crucial to act quickly, as missing this deadline almost certainly means losing your right to pursue a claim in court."
