              "content": "1. **Seek Immediate Medical Attention:** Your health is the priority. Get a thorough medical examination, even if your injuries seem minor. Follow all medical advice and attend all appointments. This also creates a crucial record for your claim. [10]\n2. **Document Everything:** Take clear, well-lit photographs of your injuries from multiple angles immediately after the accident and throughout your recovery. Keep detailed records of all medical treatments, prescriptions, therapy sessions, and related expenses. Maintain a journal to document your pain levels, emotional state, and how the injury impacts your daily life. [11]\n3. **Consult a Personal Injury Attorney:** An attorney specializing in facial injury cases can assess the strength of your claim, gather evidence, negotiate with insurance companies, and represent you in court if necessary. They can help you understand the full scope of damages you can claim. [12]\n4. **Avoid Discussing Your Case:** Do not discuss the accident or your injuries with anyone other than your attorney and medical professionals. Avoid posting about it on social media. Insurance companies may use your statements against you. [13]\n5. **Understand the Statute of Limitations:** There are strict deadlines for filing personal injury lawsuits. Your attorney can inform you of the specific time limits applicable to your case in your jurisdiction. [14]"
