          "text": "Discovery in a personal injury case typically takes several months, often ranging from six months to over a year. The exact timeline depends on your case's complexity, the court's schedule, and how well everyone cooperates. Simpler cases can be faster, while more complex ones take longer. An attorney can help make the process smoother."
