          "text": "When meeting a personal injury attorney, prioritize questions about their experience with similar cases, their fee structure (typically contingency-based), and their communication style. Ask about the potential value of your case, the legal process involved, and any challenges they foresee. Understanding their approach to negotiation versus trial, and who will directly handle your case, is crucial. This initial discussion helps you assess their expertise, transparency, and whether they are the right fit to advocate for your rights and secure the compensation you deserve, ensuring you make an informed decision during a vulnerable time."
