          "text": "A verdict is the formal decision or finding made by a jury, or by a judge in a bench trial, at the end of a legal case. It represents the conclusion of the trial proceedings, determining the rights and liabilities of the parties involved. In personal injury cases, a verdict typically declares whether the defendant is liable for the plaintiff's injuries and, if so, the amount of damages to be awarded. It is a critical moment that signifies the outcome of the legal dispute, often leading to a judgment that legally binds the parties."
